## Description
The** Digital archiving HTTP ingress **resource&nbsp;allows to interact with a Digital Archiving store via API.

> Note

For more information on how to define a Digital Archiving documents archive and its access endpoints, see: [Digital Archiving Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-store-resource-reference).

For more information on API integration, see: [Doxee Platform 3 Digital Archiving API Integration](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/Doxee+Platform+3+Digital+Archiving+API+Integration).

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Store**

**Resource**

Select the Digital Archiving Store resource that will be invoked when calling this endpoint.

> Important

If the selected store has not been deployed on the selected tenant, a warning message is displayed.

**Endpoint**

**Path**

Enter the final part of the URL path to call.

> Note

The custom path may include "/" characters within (e.g. **custompath** or **custompath/subpath**)

For example: "po-demo/2023-10";  the resulting URL will be: [*https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com*](https://da-qa-aws-frnk-1-doxee-int.cloud.doxee.com)*/****po-demo/2023-10****/process*

**Keys**

Select the [Ingress Credentials](/doxee-platform/docs/ingress-credentials-resource-reference) resource(s) to use for API authentication.

> Note

Up to 10 API keys can be used at the same time to avoid expiration issues.

**Parallel requests**

Select the maximum number of allowed requests per second. The available options are:

- 5 *(default)*

- 10

- 15

- 20

- 25

- 30

- 40

- 50

- 60

- 70

- 80

- 90

- 100

- 120

- 140

- 160

- 180

- 200

> Important

If the selected rate limit doesn't include autoscaling, a warning message is displayed. In this case, it's necessary to adjust the capacity manually.

**Extraction**

*(toggle)*

Enable this option to allow the extraction of documents and metadata from the configured Digital Archiving store.

**Request compression**

Select the compression option for the Request:

- **None**

- **Zip**

**Response content**

Select the extraction type:

- **Metadata**: The payload is an XML describing the metadata of the documents returned.

- **Metadata and documents**: The payload is an XML with the metadata and the embedded documents.

- **Metadata and documents bundle**: The payload is a ZIP file containing the metadata XML and the documents as separate files.

- **Documents**: The payload is the document (in case of single document returned), or a ZIP file containing one or more documents.

**Response compression**

Select the compression option for the Response:

- **None**

- **Zip**

**Upload**

*(toggle)*

Enable this option to allow the upload of documents and metadata from the configured Digital Archiving store.

**Removal**

*(toggle)*

Enable this option to allow the removal of documents and metadata from the configured Digital Archiving store.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
